  <title class="- topic/title ">Add an Opt-Out Link</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">You can add an opt-out link to your
	 sites to enable visitors to opt-out of all counting and content delivery. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody ">
    <context id="context_6A1D769E1AA4440797B6CD6A55E4A7DA" class="- topic/section task/context "></context>
    <steps id="steps_6742CB7C975B4052962D747D71E34C3C" class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
      <step id="step_BF5C6C42197844678387E4C564E8DCD2" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Add the following link to your site: 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">
          <p class="- topic/p ">
            <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">&lt;a
				  href="http://clientcode.tt.omtrdc.net/optout"&gt; Your Opt Out Language
				  Here&lt;/a&gt;</codeph>
          </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_FA09EAF32AEC43F9B950B887BC329E61" class="- topic/li task/step ">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Replace the 
			 <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">clientcode</codeph> text with
			 your client code, and add the text or image to be linked to the opt-out URL. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
    <result id="result_48FB621E1AB641E49E621B5716209C97" class="- topic/section task/result ">
      <p class="- topic/p ">Any visitor who clicks this link is not included in
		  any mbox requests called from their browsing sessions until they delete their
		  cookies, or for two years, whichever comes first. This works by setting a
		  cookie for the visitor called 
		  <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">disableClient</codeph> in the 
		  <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">clientcode.tt.omtrdc.net</codeph> domain. 
		</p>
      <p> Even if you use a first-party cookie implementation, the provided
		  opt-out is set via a 3rd-party cookie. If the client is using a first-party
		  cookie only, Target checks whether an opt-out cookie is set. 
		</p>
    </result>
  </taskbody>
